<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880602-0089 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Marcade Group Inc. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> MAR WNEWS </CO><IN> TNM </IN><TEXT>   Marcade Group Inc., a New York producer and importer of apparel, said it agreed definitively to sell about 17% of the company's stock to an investor group, and to name two of its members directors.    Alexander and James Goren and affiliates are to purchase 11.9 million shares of a new issue of Marcade restricted common stock for $20 million. The shares can't be sold until they are publicly registered. The Gorens are private investors and principals and vice chairmen of New York andamp; Foreign Securities Corp.    The transaction, which requires Marcade shareholder approval, is expected to be completed by Oct. 1. With the Goren brothers, the board would expand to eight members.    Marcade closed at $3, up 37.5 cents, in New York Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday. Including the new shares, Marcade would have about 70 million shares and share equivalents outstanding. </TEXT></DOC>